President Obama has declared an emergency in the state of Vermont and authorized federal aid to assist with the aftermath of Hurricane Irene. The declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to save lives and protect property. FEMA will be responsible for identifying and providing necessary equipment and resources. The federal government will fund 75 percent of emergency protective measures. Craig A. Gilbert has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk.